## Exercise 5 — `super()` with Constructor Chain (Hard)

Create:
- `Animal` → `name`, `age`
- `Pet(Animal)` → adds `owner`
- `TrainedPet(Pet)` → adds `skill`

Each class must use `super().__init__()` to pass values up the chain.
Final object should print all 4 values.

```
Expected Output:
Name: Bruno | Age: 3 | Owner: Nandha | Skill: Sit & Stay
```

